id: pm-szdc
title: Hide runtime completion helper entrypoints from the default agent-facing command surface
description: "The live 2026-07-18 root command census exposes completion-statuses, completion-tags, and completion-types as ordinary top-level commands even though they are runtime plumbing used by generated shell completion scripts. Preserve every completion capability and explicit internal invocation path, but hide these helpers from default help, compact contracts, docs, MCP discovery, and the canonical grammar budget."
type: Task
status: open
priority: 2
tags[7]: agent-ux,"area:cli","area:contracts",completion,internal-command,simplification,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-18T14:04:52.766Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-18T14:17:49.925Z"
author: codex-ecosystem-planner
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: "Default pm --help and compact contracts do not list completion-statuses, completion-tags, or completion-types; generated bash/zsh/fish completion still resolves runtime statuses, tags, and types; an explicit internal or completion-plumbing discovery path remains testable; byte-for-byte completion behavior and exit semantics are preserved; snapshots, contracts, docs, and token-budget baselines prove zero feature loss and reduced default surface."
parent: pm-n7rr
risk: low
confidence: high
