comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T14:08:35.452Z",codex-ecosystem-planner,"Creation evidence 2026-07-18: pm --help --json exposes completion-statuses, completion-tags, and completion-types as ordinary root commands with runtime-filter descriptions. All-status exact-title searches for all three returned zero items; the focused all-term search returned only closed general help/completion work. Canonical related owners are pm-e2bq, pm-mu8m, and pm-lp4j. This task removes only discovery-surface noise and explicitly preserves every completion capability."
  "2026-07-18T14:12:45.306Z",codex-ecosystem-planner,"Planning verification: focused linked suite passed 3 files / 125 tests in an isolated tracker context. Post-mutation all-status validation is ok with zero history drift; graph remains zero-actionable with no active isolates; exact/fuzzy duplicate result remains limited to the already-canceled accidental probe cluster and parent-scope duplicates remain zero. This item intentionally stays open for future implementation."
  "2026-07-18T14:17:49.925Z",codex-ecosystem-planner,"Publication: tracker planning and governance changes are proposed in GitHub PR #594 (https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/pull/594) from branch agent/command-surface-context-roadmap-governance. Review the item definition, linked evidence, and canonical roadmap notes together."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T14:12:45.990Z",codex-ecosystem-planner,"Command-surface audits must classify visibility as well as capability: a runtime helper can be correct, tested, and required by shell completion while still being harmful in default agent discovery. Contracts need an explicit public, compatibility-alias, extension-owned, or internal-plumbing visibility class so generated help cannot re-promote helpers accidentally."
