docs[1]{path,scope,note}:
  docs/COMMANDS.md,project,Public completion surface and migration documentation
body: "## Problem\nThe default root help currently advertises three runtime data providers as if agents should invoke them directly: completion-statuses, completion-tags, and completion-types. This adds three nouns to the discovery surface without adding user capability.\n\n## Desired design\nTreat these entrypoints as internal completion plumbing. The public pm completion noun remains discoverable; generated shell scripts keep a stable way to request live schema values; internal helpers are hidden from ordinary help, contracts, docs, and MCP enumeration and may be routed beneath completion verbs or an explicit internal registry.\n\n## Verification\nMeasure root-help and compact-contract token deltas; snapshot generated bash, zsh, and fish scripts; execute each completion path against built-in plus custom types, statuses, and tags; prove old helper spellings remain compatibility aliases or internal entrypoints until the grammar migration policy permits removal.\n\n## Duplicate check\nAll-status exact-title searches for each helper returned zero items. Focused all-term search for runtime resolved shell completion helper hiding found only closed general help/completion work and no focused open owner. Related scopes are pm-e2bq for tiered help, pm-mu8m for generated completion/contracts surfaces, and pm-lp4j for internal worker hiding."
